<H3> <TI>   UNITA To Propose Amendments to Government Offer </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1703073994 Luanda Radio Nacional Network in Portuguese 
0600 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1703073994 </F>
<F P=104>  Luanda Radio Nacional Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by correspondent Pedro Manuel in Lusaka] </F>
  [Text] The issue of the National Union for the Total 
Independence of Angola's [UNITA] participation in the country's 
government has not been resolved because UNITA has not yet 
responded to the government's offer. Last night, a source close 
to UNITA described as interesting the government's offer, adding 
however that UNITA was going to propose some amendments. The 
source declined to comment on the nature of such amendments, 
saying only that UNITA will today continue its meetings with the 
mediators and the observers to discuss the matter. 
  Meanwhile, another source has said that UNITA continues to 
avoid a definitive settlement to the problem and is only making 
general considerations concerning the government's offer. It is 
believed, though, that the mediators and observers want concrete 
answers from UNITA and will likely exert pressure on it today to 
obtain them. We will have to wait and see. 

</TEXT>

