<H3> <TI>   More UN Election Monitors Arrive 16 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1603185894 Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio in English 
1600 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1603185894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Another 200 UN election observers have arrived in 
South Africa and are being taught about South African 
conditions, the political scene, the media, and voter education. 
The observers are also being trained in security matters by the 
South African Defense Force and the South African Police, and in 
first aid by the Red Cross. They will be deployed throughout 
the country on Monday to monitor the election campaign. Besides 
the 500 observers already in the country, an additional 
contingent of at least 1,300 will be deployed in mid-April and 
will stay until 2 days after the election. 

</TEXT>

