<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ciskei Government Yields to Worker Demands for Pensions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1703091994 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1703091994 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Ciskeian Government has yielded to pressure by 
public servants, and has persuaded the trustees of the pension 
fund to pay out pension contributions to striking workers. The 
government said in a statement that the liquid portion of the 
fund would be paid out and that certificates would be issued to 
contributors indicating how much they would receive once the 
fixed assets had been sold. 

</TEXT>

