<F P=103> MB1803071794 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by D. Guy] </F>
  [Text] Umtata March 17 SAPA -- Former Transkei Justice 
Minister Tsepo Letlaka accepted his position as Eastern Cape 
premier designate for the Pan-Africanist Congress [PAC] at a 
lunch in Umtata on Thursday [17 March]. "The Eastern Cape 
region has a new problem of having the boundaries imposed by the 
World Trade Centre process without consulting the people in the 
region," he said. 
  "Consequently the region is still divided on whether it 
should be divided into two -- Border/Kei and Eastern Cape." 
  He said it also remained a sensitive issue whether the East 
Griqualand-Mount Currie-Umzimkulu area should be part of his 
region or kwaZulu-Natal. 

