<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   TEC Sets Up Committee To Oversee Public Funds </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB1803090594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1803090594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Transitional Executive Council's subcouncil on 
finance is to set up a control committee to ensure that public 
funds are properly spent and accounted for. This follows the 
news that four self-governing territories, Lebowa, Gazankulu, 
kaNgwane, and kwaNdebele have indicated they will overspend 
their budgets for 1993-94 by a total of 333 million rands. The 
subcouncil recommeded approval of central government guaranteed 
overdraft facilities for a total of 478 million rands. 

</TEXT>

