<H3> <TI>   CCF Meets in Maputo, Discusses Troop Confinement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2203102294 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
0600 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2203102294 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Cease-Fire Commission [CCF] has (?issued) a 
statement concerning the start of the process of destroying 
ammunition and explosive devices in government and Mozambique 
National Resistance [Renamo] troop assembly areas. 
  At a meeting in Maputo yesterday, the CCF found that the 
pace 
of government and Renamo troop confinement has dropped slightly. 
The United Nations has called on the two sides to replace 
troops as they are demobilized. 
  At a meeting to analyze the evolution of the troop 
confinement and demobilization process, Renamo presented 
complaints that men were allegedly being trained in Goba, in 
Maputo Province, and that Mozambique Armed Forces, FAM, soldiers 
were allegedly selling weapons to civilians in Tete Province. 
  The CCF promised to investigate on the ground the 
allegations 
that have been presented by the movement led by Afonso Dhlakama. 

</TEXT>

