<F P=100> WEST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Burkina Faso </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Prime Minister's Background Outlined </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB2203171794 Ouagadougou Radiodiffusion Nationale du Burkina 
Radio in French 0630 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2203171794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ouagadougou Radiodiffusion Nationale du Burkina 
Radio </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] New Prime Minister Roch Marc Christian Kabore 
yesterday granted an exclusive interview to Radio Burkina. The 
current prime minister, appointed by presidential decree, is not 
new to the political scene. He is 37 years old and has held 
successive posts as minister of transport and communications 
from 1989 to 1990, minister of state from 1990 to 1992, minister 
of state in charge of finance and planning from 1992 to 1993, 
and then minister in charge of relations with institutions. 

</TEXT>

