<H3> <TI>   Police Strike Forces Removal of Ciskei Government </TI></H3>
<H4>   Pretoria's Assistance Requested </H4>
<F P=102> MB2203170294 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1636 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2203170294 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bisho, Ciskei March 22 SAPA -- The Ciskei government 
has officially requested South African assistance to maintain 
control of the homeland. South African ambassador to Ciskei, Mr 
Piet Goosen, said on Tuesday [22 March] night that a request had 
been dispatched to Pretoria, SABC [South African Broadcasting 
Corporation] radio news reported. 
  A number of Ciskei policemen on Tuesday embarked on a strike 
and took at least five officers who they alleged were involved 
in corruption hostage. They also demanded the arrest of the 
homeland's commissioner of police. 

</TEXT>

