<H3> <TI>   Presidential Palace Surrounded by Armored Vehicles </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB2403083694 Libreville Africa No. 1 in French 0730 GMT 24 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2403083694 </F>
<F P=104>  Libreville Africa No. 1 </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Blood was shed again last night in the Burundian 
capital, where more than 1,000 people have died since the 
weekend. There is a disheartening scene in Bujumbura with 
streets strewn with mutilated bodies. 
  Meanwhile, the presidential palace has been surrounded since 
last night by Army armored vehicles. In a radio broadcast 
yesterday, President Cyprien Ntaryamira appealed for calm and 
national reconciliation, but his appeal has apparently not been 
heeded since people continued to be massacred throughout the 
night. [passage omitted] 

