<H3> <TI>   Minister Reportedly Asks France To Intervene </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA2503101794 Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania Network in Swahili 
0330 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2503101794 </F>
<F P=104>  Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Swahili </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the press review] </F>
  [Text] On Burundi, the DAILY NEWS gives prominence to a 
report in which the Burundi Government has appealed to France to 
intervene and bring to an end the military campaign to kill 
loyal Burundi citizens. The appeal was made by Leonard 
Nyangoma, the minister of internal affairs and security, who 
spoke to the DAILY NEWS by telephone from his hiding place. The 
minister, who also urged Tanzania to assist in restoring peace 
in Burundi, said the killings were continuing and that the Army 
had moved to the villages. He did not give the number of people 
who had been killed. 

</TEXT>

