<F P=100> INTER-AFRICAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nigeria's Abacha Opens Lake Chad Summit in Abuja </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB2303091594 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network in English 0600 GMT 
23 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2303091594 </F>
<F P=104>  Lagos Radio Nigeria Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The head of state, General Sani Abacha, will 
today in Abuja launch a campaign to safeguard the Lake Chad 
Basin. The launching is part of the summit of the Lake Chad 
Basin Commission, which began in the Federal Capital Territory 
yesterday. Addressing the opening session, Gen. Abacha called 
on the international community to give African nations the 
freedom to solve their internal problems. [passage omitted] 
  The Lake Chad Basin Commission, established in 1964 in 
response to the resolution of the Economic and Social Council of 
the United Nations, is a joint venture between the Governments 
of Chad, Niger, Cameroon, and Nigeria. The Chadian delegation 
to the summit is being led by President Idriss Deby while 
President Mahamane Ousmane is at the head of Niger's team. The 
minister of planning and environmental management, Mr. Augustin 
Kodock, is leading the Cameroonian team to the two-day summit. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

