<F P=100> EAST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Somalia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Points of Agreement Described </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA2403203694 Mogadishu Voice of the Somali Republic in 
Somali 1700 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2403203694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mogadishu Voice of the Somali Republic </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Somali </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] The agreement contains two 
sections: general principles and the new administration. 
  The general principles section deals with the inviolable 
respect for and sovereignty of the Somali people; opposing the 
use of force to resolve anything; implementation of the 
cease-fire and voluntary disarmament; respect for and 
preservation of human and democratic rights; creation of 
suitable conditions to enable the Somali people to coexist 
fraternally in line with their traditions, culture and politics; 
and rehabilitation and reconstruction of the country to enable 
it to rise out of the destruction of the civil war. 
  The second section of the agreement provides for the 
formation of an administration: The restoration of peace to 
Somalia, giving priorities to trouble spots; the holding in 
Mogadishu of a conference to be attended by the signatories to 
the Addis Ababa agreement and the Somali National Movement on 15 
April this year; the drafting of election laws and procedures; 
and methods for participating in the national reconciliation 
conference. The conference will deliberate on modalities for 
forming a national council charged with drafting laws, to be 
formed after a national government has been formed in order to 
restore our country's dignity and nationhood. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

