<F P=100> EAST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Somalia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aidid, Ali Mahdi Comment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA2403190094 Nairobi KBC Television Network in English 1600 
GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2403190094 </F>
<F P=104>  Nairobi KBC Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Rival Somali clan leaders General Mohamed Farah 
Aidid and Ali Mahdi Mohamed today signed an agreement to end the 
civil war in Somalia. They will also try to establish a central 
government. The two leaders signed the reconciliation agreement 
after two weeks of talks in Nairobi. UN officials said that the 
announcement of the declaration is a breakthrough in the Somali 
peace talks, which had been deadlocked for months. The Somali 
leaders said they will implement their declaration on the 
restoration of peace in Somalia. 
  [Begin recording] [Aidid, in Somali] Our country has 
suffered destruction. 
  [Unidentified translator, in English] We all know that a 
very heavy tragedy and destruction faced our country. The only 
way to finish off that problem for Somali people is to solve the 
differences which have been caused by the civil war. 
  [Ali Mahdi, in English] Presence of the Somali leaders here 
today is a clear manifestation of the closing and the (?harsh) 
of historical chapter and the opening of a new [words 
indistinct] enthusiasm and hope which will permit us to address 
seriously on the issues of our national reconciliation process. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

