<F P=100> EAST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Uganda </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister on Completion of Election Arrangements </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA2403210594 Kampala Radio Uganda Network in English 1700 
GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2403210594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kampala Radio Uganda Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The minister of state for internal affairs, Mr. 
Tom Butime, has assured members of the joint international 
observer group, who have started arriving in the country for the 
Constituent Assembly elections which will take place on Monday 
[28 March] that the government has put everything in place to 
ensure that the elections take place unhindered. Mr. Butime, 
together with the Constituent Assembly commissioner and 
officials of the UN independent secretariat and the UNDP 
[National Union for Democracy and Progress], were briefing the 
observers on the situation on the ground at a pre-deployment 
meeting, which took place at the city hall this afternoon. Mr. 
Butime told them that it is in the interests of the government 
to ensure that the elections on Monday succeed, because the 
stakes are high and everything has been finalized to ensure 
their freedom of movement and access to the areas that they will 
want to visit. He assured them that the security of Uganda is 
good and that nothing will hinder the elections on polling day. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

