<H3> <TI>   CAR, UTD Agree on Choice of Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB2403133494 Lome Radio Lome in French 1230 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB2403133494 </F>
<F P=104>  Lome Radio Lome </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by CAR Chairman Yaovi Agboyibor in Lome on </F>
24 March; read by Afan Houenoumadje--recorded] 
  [Text] [Begin Houenoumadje recording] The Action Committee 
for Renewal [CAR] is satisfied with the fact that the Togolese 
Union for Democracy's [UTD] letter to the CAR chairman stressed 
the need for the two opposition political parties, which 
constitute the parliamentary majority, to agree on the 
distribution of responsibilities at the head of the institutions 
to be put in place after the 6 and 20 February legislative 
elections. In reaction to that letter, the UTD and CAR chairmen 
each accompanied by one aide met the same day at 1530 to put 
finishing touches to their discussions on the choice of a prime 
minister. The two parties agreed that the CAR should propose 
one of its activists to take up the prime ministerial post. 
Following this agreement the CAR proposed a name that was then 
accepted by the UTD. The two political parties are now waiting 
for the head of state's invitation to a meeting in order to 
convey the name to him. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

