<F P=101> Angola </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNITA Claims South African Mercenaries Killed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2503070294 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in 
Portuguese 0600 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2503070294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Communique issued by the General Staff of the Armed Forces </F>
for the Liberation of Angola in Huambo on 21 March] 
  [Text] 1. In Lunda Norte, South African mercenaries have 
met the appropriate response to their adventure of 16 March 1994 
when they carried out an attack in the area between Lufige and 
Luxa Rivers, resulting in the death of 12 white South African 
mercenaries. They were led by Lieutenant (Stein Marais) and 
Noncommissioned Officer (Bronoz). Captured documents revealed 
that additional groups are being deployed in the region. 
  2. The Russian aircraft impounded in Rundu, Namibia, are 
owned by the Futungo [Angolan Government] and have nothing to do 
with the National Union for the Total Independence of Angola 
[UNITA]. The pilots are Angolan and Portuguese nationals. The 
Namibian Government is hereby challenged to take the crew to one 
of its tribunals so that the world may know the truth. 
  3. Until a general and verifiable cease-fire is declared, 
the MPLA [Popular Movement for the Liberation of Angola] will 
seize no more UNITA-occupied positions without receiving the 
appropriate response. Military adventures must come to an end. 
  [Dated] Huambo, 21 March 1994 
  [Signed] Army General Arlindo Chenda Isaac Pena Ben-Ben, 
chief of the General Staff 

</TEXT>

