<H3> <TI>   UNITA Reportedly Kidnaps 3 South Africans </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2503080094 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0658 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2503080094 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pretoria March 25 SAPA -- Three employees of the 
South African-based Executive Outcomes CC are believed to have 
been kidnapped by UNITA [National Union for the Total 
Independence of Angola] rebels in Angola, a statement by the 
company's lawyers in Pretoria said on Friday [25 March]. 
  The statement by Wilsenach, Van Wyk, Goosen and Bekker said 
the employees were believed to have been kidnapped by UNITA on 
Wednesday while investigating "criminal activities" near the 
company's training area in Angola. "The next of kin of the 
three members have been notified. Currently a large-scale 
operation is being conducted by the company and assistance is 
being rendered by the Angolan armed forces," the statement 
added. More information would be released later. 
  Executive Outcomes provides security services in Angola. 

</TEXT>

